featured.text: What are the characteristics of Jeanie’s Kiddie Stool? (A) Permanent and foldable.
Why did Jeanie Low invent the Kiddie Stool, according to the passage?
Jeanie called her invention the “Kiddie Stool.”
Using metal hinges, Jeanie attached one piece of the wood to the front of the cabinet door, and the second piece to the first.

other.text: Jeanie’s Kiddie Stool won first place in her school’s contest.
Which of the following sayings best captures the spirit of Jeanie Low’s story? (A) Failure is the mother of success.
As a result, Jeanie was invited to make a number of public appearances with her Kiddie Stool, and was featured on local TV as well as in newspapers.

definition.zh_def: 一種女性名字，通常是Jean的變體。
definition.en_def: A female given name, often a variant of Jean.
definition.example: Jeanie loves to paint in her free time.
